audit:
Run the following script to verify Banner is set:
{
   #!/usr/bin/env bash

   source /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config 2>/dev/null
   source /etc/sysconfig/sshd 2>/dev/null
   sshd -T $OPTIONS $CRYPTO_POLICY | grep -Pi -- '^banner\h+\/\H+'
}
Example output:
Banner /etc/issue.net
- IF - Match set statements are used in your environment, specify the connection parameters to use for the -T extended test mode and run the audit to verify the setting is not incorrectly configured in a match block
Example additional audit needed for a match block for the user sshuser:
{
   #!/usr/bin/env bash

   source /etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/opensshserver.config
   source /etc/sysconfig/sshd
   sshd -T $OPTIONS $CRYPTO_POLICY -C user=sshuser | grep -Pi -- '^banner\h+\/\H+'
}
